nts1.n: The Trilogy Tapes w/ Basic Rhythm (R)
nts1.d: Clandestine record label, The Trilogy Tapes, tear up the NTS studios once a month, ripping through the grittiest and muddiest tracks. No words on this one, just tunes.
Artist Peter J Doyle & friends enter the uncanny valley of their music collections, traversing folk, soul, psychedelia and much more…

Desire paths are formed by repeated deviation from official routes.
Artist/producer Laura Groves explores private roads and dreamscapes with a series of mixtapes featuring demos, synth sketches, collaborations, pop classics, field recordings and soundtracks.
"Raga Vibrations" is a monthly selection of Indian music curated by Greg Davis.

nts1.n: THE ONE GLOVE BREAKFAST SHOW W/ MACCA
nts1.d: Stay left and take a trip with Macca's Saturday breakfast show on NTS. Weekend musings and eclectic cuts from all over the place, it's a low-key affair and you're all invited. ONE GLOVE!!!
Eglo Records' main man Alexander Nut joins us for some slick late night futurism. Broken beat, soul, and whatever else happens to take his fancy.

nts1.n: GILDED SOUND REFLECTION - OFF THE SHELF VOL. 18
nts1.d:
Gilded Sound Reflection is the musical collective of Tai Thittichai and David Lane. They magnify the bleed between genre lines, blurring the boundaries of krautrock, jazz, psych, soul, pop and more – a monthly show, settle in for a meandering couple hours early in the afternoon.
From the host: "GSR continues its mixed media journey with a second show to combine records and CD's found in the wild. A nostalgic throwback of music and stories for a Saturday afternoon."
Kit Records founder Richard Greenan offers a tropical hangover tonic of off-beam electronics, weird field recordings and feel good pop wonk. Old, new, borrowed, blue.

Lex Records artist Boom Bip scrapes beneath the surface of the status quo by loosely basing his mixes on electronics and the new waves they produce.

Kaili brings you the practice of Bodywork, an hour-long cleansing ritual of club music traversing time and locality, applying pressure where it's needed in order to release…
From the host: "an eclectic, moody, bass-driven mix inspired by new ambient and experimental pop/rap/drill + some dubstep influences. a wintry slow walk into a basement dancefloor."

American dance music, field recording related music and beyond. Played live.

nts2.n: LOST IN THE BITRATE W/ LENA RAINE (R)
nts2.d: Video game composer Lena Raine explores sounds of digital – playing digital fusion, electronica, and modern orchestral works that blend live and digital sounds.

If you're feeling charitable, you can say I am nostalgic, if you're being ungenerous, you can say I am being lazy…a hour long mix of tracks already played on this residency. 
“The advantage of a bad memory is that one enjoys several times the same good things for the first time.”
― Friedrich Nietzsche.
The revered Japanese noise artist stops by for a regular NTS slot, playing some surprising selections from his diverse & deep record collection.

nts2.d:
Stories unfold on the upper floor, carried by a multitude of voices. French radio, the seventies, women’s voices, and carelessness. 
Music & Sound Supervision by Souleymane Said
Irregular extra special shows from the world of Melbourne reissue label Efficient Space.
Mikey Young of Total Control and Eddie Current Suppression Ring plays a selection of 60's and 70's soft rock…

nts2.n: TAFELMUSIK W/ FRANCESCO FUSARO - Morton Feldman Anniversary
nts2.d:
Francesco Fusaro, the man behind MFZ Records and classical music recording series 19'40'', brings a considered and varied selection of baroque, classical and contemporary music for a full two hours each month.
From the host: "Tafelmusik marks Morton Feldman’s centenary: a giant of modern composition, close to the New York School and painters like Mark Rothko and Philip Guston."

Hannah Catherine Jones splits things open for the Opera Show: an exploration of the best in opera old and new, as well as an unearthing of the operatic in other records from soul, jazz or further afield.
From the host: "This episode marks 10 years of The Opera Show and is the first of an ongoing series celebrating the life of my dad - Roy Durban Jones - who taught me and many, many others so much about music, including opera, and who sadly passed away recently."

“I start associating your voice with ….”, for a while ML has been part of the NTS community, jingling around, airing his monthly 150 Session out of Berlin’s North, where all seasons give reasons. For clarification, creation, inspiration. One hour of poetic and musical explorations, questions, and curiosities. Circling around daring electronics, ethno-sonics, jazz-constructivism, minimalism, open structured digital dopamine, risky dub excitement and other sounds, that still need to be written. No country, no flag – outernational without a cause!
From the host: "The first 150 Session in 2026 is dedicated to guitar and trumpet player Günter Schickert, who passed shortly before Christmas. The world darlings his kraut-historic solo work “Samtvogel”, it will echo forever. Here some rather unheard sides, showcasing his spiritual experimental reverberations."

subtle.d: Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.
